      "timestamp": "2025-11-19T18:08:10.04+00:00",
      "timestampEdited": null,
      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "Super cool! \n\nNewbie question: why is the sdram exposed via pins? to allow loading the memory/program externally directly instead of over something like uart?\n\nalso what are the 20 some \"blocks\" in the image?",
      "author": {
        "id": "384390069412429834",
        "name": "polyfractal",
        "discriminator": "0000",
        "nickname": "BreakingTaps",
        "color": null,
        "isBot": false,
        "roles": [],
        "avatarUrl": "2025-11_media/8d8c1d8b8ad51d6cdb1a47512c39b297-42908.png"
      },
      "attachments": [],
