      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "I mean, I did build the Tiny Tapeout Micro Linux SoC. With that thing I could boot Linux with just 8 MB. The SoC should support IPv6 and IPv4 and be comfortable to use — not just boot BusyBox and call it a day. I want to do more with it: MicroPython, C++, NFS, all kinds of stuff.",
